RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Special Weight Purse 80000. (UP TO $13,920 NYSBFOA) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BALPOOL tracked the pace while coaxed along on the outside, came under stronger encouragement near the nine-sixteenths, issued a challenge in the three path around the turn, spun four wide into the stretch then took the lead under a drive around the three-sixteenths, lugged in into the final furlong, fought gamely outside of the runner-up to the wire and narrowly prevailed under good handling. CHECK ENGINE LIGHT veered out at the start but was quickly corrected, pressed the pace on the outside of the leader, vied between foes in the two path on the turn, gained the lead inside the five-sixteenths, lost the advantage to the winner in the three path near the three-sixteenths, fought inside that foe while tight against the rail in the final furlong and was denied while clear for the place. GIFTED bumped with a rival at the start, was well placed while rated just off the pace, drafted in the two path while in dead-aim of the leading trio around the turn, shifted four wide outside the quarter-pole then gained five wide into the stretch, made an outside bid around the three-sixteenths, battled outside of the top two while remaining on her inside lead into the final furlong and was outfinished while well clear for the show. TRYINMYHEARTOUT bumped with a rival at the start, went to the front, showed the way in hand with company to her outside, vied inside on the turn, was asked at the five-sixteenths then headed shortly thereafter, dropped back in the two path into upper stretch and capitulated. RIVER OAKS broke out then stumbled, dropped well behind under urging, went around most of the turn in the three path then dropped to the two path and trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Tryinmyheartout
ENTRY.COMMENT: bmpd brk,pace in hand,let out rail turn,headed ins5/16,2p1/4,wknd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SYNONYMOUS broke out at the start and was corrected, chased three then two wide coming under coaxing near the three-eighths and advancing to take command nearing the quarter pole, spun three then two wide into upper stretch, drew clear under a drive to prevail. APRIL ANTICS chased two then three wide under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, angled four to five wide for home, proved no match for the top one while along well clear and much the best of the rest. SWEET SENSATION got bumped at the start by the veering out TEKILA and was forced to steady in behind CRYSTAL ORB, chased just off the inside under a ride from the seven-sixteenths, swung four wide into upper stretch and passed tired rivals. CRYSTAL ORB established the front shortly after the start and knocked heads with AMERICA'S PRIDE, shook off that rival showing the way tucked to the inside through the turn and came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths under challenge from the eventual winner, yielded the front near the quarter pole and took the inside route into upper stretch, then tired in the drive. TEKILA veered out at the start bumping SWEET SENSATION in behind CRYSTAL ORB, chased along the inside under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, spun three wide for home and tired. AMERICA'S PRIDE shied out at the start filling the space left vacant by TEKILA who veered out, came under coaxing and advanced to knock heads with CRYSTAL ORB while along the inside down the backstretch, got shaken off into the turn and tipped to the two path placed to coaxing at the three-eighths, continued just off the inside into upper stretch and folded.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2-3w, coaxed 7/16, 4-5w upper, no match, second best

ENTRY.COMMENT: shied out st, coaxed, dueled ins, 2p turn, 2w 1/4p, folded

ENTRY.COMMENT: veered out st, chased ins, coaxed 7/16, 3w upper, tired

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, steadied st, chased 2p, 4w upper, passed tired rivals

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Ruthless S. AQUEDUCT RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 87. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Non-Lasix Race pursuant to 4043.2 (7)(e)(5) Lasix not permitted within 48 hours of post time. By subscription of $100 each which should accompany the nominations; $500 to pass the entry box and an additional $500 to start. For horses not originally nominated, a supplemental nomination payment of $500 in addition to the entry and starting fees can be made at any time prior to the closing of entries. The purse to be divided 55% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 12% to t hird, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth and 3% divided equally amongst the remaining finishers. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners of a sweepstake other than State-bred allowed 2 lbs.; of a race other than maiden, claiming, starter or State-bred allowance allowed 4 lbs . A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Saturday, January 21, 2023 with 13 Nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INTERPOLATE was taken up nearing the three-quarter pole then rated off the pace, started the turn in the two path then shifted four wide, issued a challenge with three furlongs to run, gained the lead into upper stretch, shook clear into the final furlong and proved best under steady urging. GIRL TROUBLE disputed the pace on the inside of an opponent, vied inside to the two path on the turn, was asked for her best in upper stretch, lost touch with the winner into the final furlong and was outfinished while clear for the place. MALIBU MOONSHINE was last to commence while a bit awkward into stride, settled at the rear on the outside, was urged three to four wide around the turn and lacked the needed response while able to get third. ROYAL POPPY contested the pace on the outside then in the three path on the turn, led past the quarter-pole then lost the advantage to the winner into upper stretch and gave way. SENIOR PRANK broke in and hit the gate, moved up to race just off the pace on the inside, was asked while saving ground on the turn, came off the rail into upper stretch and had nothing left.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAKE ROCKS coaxed from the gate, dueled inside of QUICKFLASH, cut the corner into upper stretch put to a drive, took over narrow command a furlong out, dug in gamely to fend off a trio and prevail on the wire. SYNTHESIS hustled from the gate, chased three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, continued three wide into upper stretch and missed at the end while up to dead heat for the place honors. FAMISHED chased four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, continued four wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive and missed at the end while dead heating for the place honors. QUICKFLASH coaxed from the start, dueled from the two path with JAKE ROCKS to his inside, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, continued just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in and was headed a furlong out, fought on to the finish but was out-finished in the late stages. ALCOOLS coaxed from the gate, chased just off the inside under a ride from the three-eighths, spun three wide for home, offered up a mild bid but was outkicked. MONEY IN THE BANK chased three wide under a ride from the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch and weakened. CAERUS chased three then two wide under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, angled five to six wide into upper stretch and came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COOL QUARTET was bumped on both sides at the start, tracked the pace on the outside, made a bid in the four path around the turn, took the lead passing the five-sixteenths, kicked clear into upper stretch and drew away under strong urging. PERCEIVED was urged along off the pace, moved closer late on the backstretch, chased inside to the two path around the turn, swung five wide into the stretch and safely secured the place. BINGO JOHN was forced out at the start then bumped with foes, raced outside under urging, went four wide around the turn, floated six wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response while along for the show. WARRIOR IN CHIEF broke out and made light contact with a foe then was hustled, showed early speed then switched out outside the five-eighths, moved up to prompt the pace, was urged along in the three path around the turn, dropped back into upper stretch then moved out and tired. DARK STORM bumped with a foe at the start then was hustled, moved in while going to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, lost the lead in the two path on the turn, dropped back into upper stretch and gave way. HAGLER was urged along towards the rear, saved ground on the turn and failed to respond. BUSTIN THE RULES was urged along at the rear, went three wide around the turn, came four wide into the stretch and faltered then was pulled up just inside the furlong marker before being vanned off.

PER DIEM three wide in pursuit, advanced on the leader under coaxing from the three-eighths, spun three wide for home, dug in under a drive proving no match for the top one while running on to secure the place honors. VOLKERT chased three then two wide down the backstretch before tucking inside through the turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, tipped out four to five wide at the three-sixteenths and kept on to secure the show honors. RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOURBONIC was bumped on both sides at the start then checked while pinched back, spotted the front several lengths, settled on the outside, was roused four then five wide on the turn, rallied outside into the stretch, closed strongly to get the lead coming to the furlong marker and proved best under strong urging. SHERIFF BIANCO dropped in at the start then bumped with a foe, tracked the pace on the outside, came under urging late on the backstretch, chased in the four path around the turn, took the lead in upper stretch, lost the advantage to the winner nearing the furlong marker, fought on with that foe while remaining on his inside lead to the wire and missed while well clear for the place. UNCLE MOONLIGHT stalked the pace on the inside, tossed his head at the nine-sixteenths and was taken up briefly, took the lead under urging while along the rail early on the turn, lost the advantage to the winner in upper stretch, dropped back into the final furlong and weakened but held the show. WINIT bumped with a rival at the start, steadied while taken under a tight hold early then moved out under vigorous restraint, was rated on the outside, came under urging in the five path on the turn, chased outside into the stretch and capitulated. REGGAE MUSIC MAN settled off the pace, was roused in the two path on the turn and failed to respond. BACK RING LUCK bumped with foes at the start, went to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, was headed while in the three path early on the turn, dropped back into the stretch and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 45000. (UP TO $7,830 NYSBFOA) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: FUNNY JOKE broke in a step at the start bumping the bobbling ONE WHIRLWIND RIDE, chased three to four wide until tucked to the two path through the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun three wide for home, rallied to issue a challenge through the final furlong and overhauled the leader seventy yards from home, then edged away to the finish. ONE WHIRLWIND RIDE bobbled and was bumped at the start, chased three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick to secure the place honors. TURNSANDCONDITIONS chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, went six wide into upper stretch, kicked on belatedly to secure the show honors. FENWAY showed the way in hand just off the inside, shook away three furlongs from home to a good lead, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in under a drive under growing threat from a trio and getting a bit leg weary near the sixteenth marker, got overhauled with seventy yards to the finish when weakening in the late stages. HANG TIGHT devoid of speed early on, quickly grew detached at the tail of the field chasing in the two path, remained two to three wide through the turn, went four wide into upper stretch and closed in under a drive but too late to impact the outcome. WINNERS LAUGH chased four paths off the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn under coaxing from the three-eighths, continued just off the inside into upper stretch and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WRITER'S REGRET tracked the pace on the outside, chased in the three path around the turn, pursued the leader under a drive into the final furlong, gained the advantage outside the sixteenth-pole then edged clear under strong urging. AGILITY chased the pace down the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, was driven into the stretch in the two path, remained on his inside lead in pursuit of the leader, moved out around the furlong marker, gained while still on his inside lead into the final sixteenth and missed while able to get the place. MY MAN MATTY brushed with a foe shortly after the start, showed the way down the backstretch, went around the turn in the two path, was asked turning into the stretch, led under a drive into the final furlong, was collared by the winner outside the sixteenth-pole and weakened while clear for the show. GOLDEN CODE moved out while urged along, went three then four wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. BASIS RISK was urged along at the rear, moved from the two path to the four path midway through the turn then dropped back to the two path and was no factor. TIN PAN ALLEY bumped with a rival at the start, moved out under urging, shifted further out late on the backstretch, chased in the four path around the turn and capitulated. DAUFUSKIE ISLAND bumped with an opponent at the start then was hustled, settled off the pace, was urged three wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch and failed to respond.
